:Class UserSettings
‚ćĚ By instanciating this class you get a representation of a user settings file required by Tatin.\\
‚ćĚ In case no path pointing to a folder hosting such a file is provided to `‚éēNEW`, the file is searched
‚ćĚ for (and created if it does not yet exist) in the default location (user's home folder) which
‚ćĚ depends on your operating system.\\
‚ćĚ You may call `‚éēSE.Tatin.GetUserHomeFolder ''` in order to establish that location.\\
‚ćĚ Optionally you may specify a folder hosting the configuration file as an argument to `‚éēNEW`.\\
‚ćĚ Again, if the file does not yet exist it will be created with defaults.\\
‚ćĚ After having created an instance you can add a Registry definition (read: an instance of the
‚ćĚ `DefineRegistry` class) to the user settings with `AddRegistry`, and you may also call
‚ćĚ `ReplaceRegistry` and `RemoveRegistry`.\\
‚ćĚ Note that all changes are strictly workspace-only. If you want your changes to be written to file
‚ćĚ you must call the `Save` method with a 1 as right argument. The exception is that when the file
‚ćĚ does not yet exist, it is created and written to disk with defaults.\\
‚ćĚ If you have passed to `‚éēNEW` a path to where the user settings file should be created, and you want
‚ćĚ this file to become the default user settings file whenever Dyalog APL is fired up, then make a call
‚ćĚ to the `MakeDefaultFile` instance method. This creates (or overwrites) a file '.tatin` that points
‚ćĚ to that folder.\\
‚ćĚ The full name of the file is available via the field `path2config`.\\
‚ćĚ You may convert a particular Registry into an ordinary namespace by calling the `GetRegistry` method.

    :Field Public Shared ReadOnly cfg_name‚Üź'tatin-client.json'  ‚ćĚ Name of the user config file is fixed
    :Field Public Shared ReadOnly ErrorNo‚Üź997                   ‚ćĚ Used by `Assert`

    ‚ąá make0;configFile;buff
      :Implements Constructor
      :Access Public
      Init1 ‚ć¨
      configFile‚Üźhome.GetUserHomeFolder'.tatin'
      :If F.IsFile configFile                               ‚ćĚ Has the user...
          buff‚Üź(‚ąä1‚äÉF.NGET configFile)~‚éēTC
      :AndIf 0<‚ČĘbuff                                        ‚ćĚ ... specified her own location for the user settings file?
          _path2config‚ÜźAddSlash buff                        ‚ćĚ Then we accept that
      :Else
          _path2config‚ÜźAddSlash home.GetUserHomeFolder ‚ć¨    ‚ćĚ By default it's the user's home folder on all platforms
      :EndIf
      :If F.IsFile _path2config,cfg_name                    ‚ćĚ If it exists...
          Read ‚ć¨                                            ‚ćĚ we read it
      :Else
          AddPrincipalServer ‚ć¨
          AddTestServer ‚ć¨
          Save 1
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá make1(path2config_);reg;buff
      :Implements Constructor
      :Access Public
      Init1 ‚ć¨
       ‚ćĚ In case the user passed the fully qualified name rather than just the folder:
      :If cfg_name{‚ćļ‚Č°(-‚ČĘ‚ćļ)‚ÜĎ‚ćĶ}path2config_
          path2config_‚Üź(-‚ČĘcfg_name)‚Üďpath2config_
      :EndIf
      'Is not a directory?!'Assert F.IsDir path2config_
      _path2config‚ÜźAddSlash path2config_
      :If F.IsFile path2config
          Read ‚ć¨
          _registries‚Üź{0<‚äÉ‚ćĶ.‚éēNC'proxy':‚ćĶ ‚čĄ ‚ćĶ.proxy‚Üź'' ‚čĄ ‚ćĶ}¬®_registries  ‚ćĚ "proxy" was introduced in 0.96.0
      :Else
          AddPrincipalServer ‚ć¨
          AddTestServer ‚ć¨
          Save 1
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá Init1 dummy
    ‚ćĚ Early initialisation
      home‚Üź(‚äÉ‚äÉ‚éēCLASS ‚éēTHIS).##
      F‚Üźhome.F ‚čĄ A‚Üźhome.A
      _source‚Üź''
      _registries‚Üź‚ć¨
      _caching‚Üź1
      _path2cache‚Üź''
      _license‚Üź''
      _group‚Üź''
      _maintainer‚Üź''
    ‚ąá

    :Property source
    ‚ćĚ Defines the default for the "source" property of a new package.\\
    ‚ćĚ Setting this might be useful in case you use most of the time the same source folder, so it makes
    ‚ćĚ sense to pre-populate a package's "source" property with a default defined here.
    :Access Public Instance
        ‚ąá r‚Üźget
          r‚Üź_source
        ‚ąá
        ‚ąá set value;buff
          buff‚Üźvalue.NewValue
          'Invalid: "source"; (depth)'Assert 1=‚Č°buff
          'Invalid: "source"; (data type)'Assert' '=1‚ÜĎ0‚ćībuff
          _source‚Üźbuff
        ‚ąá
    :EndProperty

    :Property path2config
    :Access Public Instance
        ‚ąá r‚Üźget
          r‚Üź_path2config,cfg_name
        ‚ąá
    :EndProperty

    :Property fileTimestamp
    ‚ćĚ Returns the file timestamp. Used to detect changes made in one way or another.
    :Access Public Instance
        ‚ąá r‚Üźget
          r‚Üź_fileTimestamp
        ‚ąá
    :EndProperty

    :Property registries
    :Access Public Instance
        ‚ąá r‚Üźget
          :If 0=‚ČĘ_registries
              r‚Üź_registries
          :Else
              r‚Üź_registries[‚ćí_registries.priority]
          :EndIf
        ‚ąá
    :EndProperty

    :Property json
    :Access Public Instance
        ‚ąá r‚Üźget
          r‚ÜźGetJSON5
        ‚ąá
    :EndProperty

    :Property caching
    ‚ćĚ A Boolean that decides whether packages that are loaded or installed are saved to
    ‚ćĚ or read from the Tatin cache.
    :Access Public Instance
        ‚ąá r‚Üźget
          r‚Üź_caching
        ‚ąá
        ‚ąá set val
          'Invalid: "caching"; must be a Boolean'Assert(‚äāval.NewValue)‚ąä0 1
          _caching‚Üźval.NewValue
        ‚ąá
    :EndProperty

    :Property path2cache
    ‚ćĚ Defines the path where the Tatin package cache lives.
    ‚ćĚ If this is empty then the path is established with defaults that depend on the operating system
    :Access Public Instance
        ‚ąá r‚Üźget
          r‚Üź_path2cache
        ‚ąá
        ‚ąá set val
          'Invalid: "patch2cache"; must be a simpe char vector'Assert(‚Č°val.NewValue)‚ąä0 1
          'Invalid: "patch2cache";  must be a simple char vector'Assert' '=1‚ÜĎ0‚ćīval.NewValue
          _path2cache‚Üźval.NewValue
        ‚ąá
    :EndProperty

