    ‚ąá {r}‚ÜźAddRegistry y;registry;name;alias;buff;reg;isZero;ind;newPriorities
   ‚ćĚ Adds the definition of a Registry (from a namespace or an instance of the DefineRegistry class)
   ‚ćĚ to the user settings.\\
   ‚ćĚ If a Registry with the same uri&alias is already defined an error is thrown.\\
   ‚ćĚ `‚ćĶ` must be one of:
   ‚ćĚ * An instance of the "Registry" class.
   ‚ćĚ * A text vector with a name or an alias+name in the format `[alias]name`\\
   ‚ćĚ   In this case `AddRegistry` creates an instance on the fly. Of course this means that this is
   ‚ćĚ   only suitable in case specifying just the name and optionally the alias is sufficient.
   ‚ćĚ * A namespace that can be used to instantiate the `DefineRegistry` class.\\
   ‚ćĚ `‚Üź` is always `‚ć¨` (shy).
      :Access Public Instance
      r‚Üź‚ć¨
      :If 80=‚éēDR y
          :If ‚ąß/'[]'‚ąäy
              (alias name)‚Üź{‚ćĶ{('[]'~‚ć®‚ćĶ‚ÜĎ‚ćļ)(‚ćĶ‚Üď‚ćļ)}‚ćĶ‚ć≥']'}y
              alias‚Üź‚éēC alias
          :Else
              name‚Üźy
              alias‚Üź''
          :EndIf
          ((name='\')/name)‚Üź'/'
          registry‚Üź‚éēNEW home.DefineRegistry(,‚äāname)
          registry.alias‚Üź‚éēC alias
      :ElseIf ‚ą®/'[DefineRegistry]'‚ć∑‚ćēy ‚ćĚ Instance of the class "DefineRegistry"?
          registry‚Üźy
      :Else
          registry‚Üź‚éēNEW home.DefineRegistry(,‚äāy)
      :EndIf
      :If 0<‚ČĘ_registries
          'This URI/alias combination is already defined'Assert~(‚äāregistry.(uri alias))‚ąä_registries.(uri alias)
          :If 0<registry.‚éēNC'alias'
          :AndIf 0<‚ČĘregistry.alias
              'This alias is already used for a different uri'Assert~(‚äāregistry.alias)‚ąä_registries.alias
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
      :If ‚ą®/'[DefineRegistry]'‚ć∑‚ćēregistry
          buff‚Üźregistry.Get ‚ć¨
      :Else
          buff‚Üźregistry
      :EndIf
      :If 0=buff.‚éēNC'priority'
      :OrIf ‚éēNULL=buff.priority
          :If 0=‚ČĘ_registries
              buff.priority‚Üź100
          :Else
              isZero‚Üź_registries.priority‚Č°¬®0
              :If 0‚Č•buff.priority‚Üź(‚Ćä/_registries.priority~0 ‚éēNULL)-10
              :AndIf 0‚Č•buff.priority‚Üź‚Ćä(‚Ćä/_registries.priority~0 ‚éēNULL)√∑2
              :AndIf 0‚Č•buff.priority‚Üź‚Ćą(‚Ćä/_registries.priority~0 ‚éēNULL)-1
              ‚ćĚ We need to make room
                  ind‚Üź‚ćč_registries.priority
                  newPriorities‚Üź100√ó1+‚ć≥‚ČĘ_registries.priority[ind]
                  (isZero[ind]/newPriorities)‚Üź0                     ‚ćĚ Restore zeros
                  _registries.priority‚Ćą‚ÜźnewPriorities[‚ćčind]
                  buff.priority‚Üź100
              :EndIf
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
      buff.uri‚ÜźAddSlash buff.uri
      buff.noCaching‚Üźregistry.noCaching  ‚ćĚ This IS required, otherwise it won't work though it should
      _registries,‚Üźbuff
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá r‚Üź{rawFlag}ListRegistries showApiKey
    ‚ćĚ List all data of all registries.\\
    ‚ćĚ `showApiKey` must be a flag. If it 1 then the API key is shown, otherwise it is replaced by "***"
    ‚ćĚ With `rawflag` being 0 (the default) the result is beautified.
      :Access Public Instance
      rawFlag‚Üź{0<‚éēNC ‚ćĶ:‚ćé‚ćĶ ‚čĄ 0}'rawFlag'
      '‚ćĶ must be a Boolean'Assert(‚äārawFlag)‚ąä0 1
      r‚Üź‚ÜĎregistries.(alias uri port priority noCaching api_key)
      :If (,1)‚ČĘ,showApiKey
          r[;2‚äÉ‚ćīr]‚Üź‚äā'***'          ‚ćĚ Replace API key by Asterisks
      :EndIf
      :If ~rawFlag
          r‚Üź((,[0.5]'Alias' 'URI' 'Port' 'Priority' '~caching' 'API-key'),[1]' ')‚ć™r
          r[2;]‚Üź(‚Ćą‚ĆŅ‚ČĘ¬®r)‚ćī¬®'-'
      :EndIf
    ‚ćĚDone
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá {r}‚ÜźReplaceRegistry registry;ind;reg;priority
   ‚ćĚ Replaces the definition of a Registry in the user settings.\\
   ‚ćĚ If that Registry does not already exist an error is thrown.\\
   ‚ćĚ `‚ćĶ` must be an instance of the "Registry" class.\\
   ‚ćĚ `‚Üź` is always `‚ć¨` (shy).
      :Access Public Instance
      r‚Üź‚ć¨
      'There is no such registry yet'Assert 0<‚ČĘ_registries
      :If 0>registry.‚éēNC‚äā'id'    ‚ćĚ Old stuff might lack ID (introduced with 0.74.0)
          ind‚Üź_registries.id‚ć≥‚äāregistry.id
      :Else
          ind‚Üź_registries.uri‚ć≥‚äāregistry.uri
      :EndIf
      'There is no such registry yet'Assert(‚ČĘ_registries)‚Č•ind
      :If ‚ą®/'[DefineRegistry]'‚ć∑‚ćēregistry  ‚ćĚ Instance of the "DefineRegistry" class?
          priority‚Üź_registries[ind].priority
          _registries[ind]‚Üźregistry.Get ‚ć¨
          :If ‚éēNULL‚Č°_registries[ind].priority
              _registries[ind].priority‚Üźpriority ‚ćĚ Inherit from predecessor
          :EndIf
      :Else
          reg‚Üź‚éēNEW home.DefineRegistry(,‚äāregistry)
          _registries[ind]‚Üźreg.Get ‚ć¨
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá flag‚ÜźExist uriOrAlias
    ‚ćĚ Checks whether `uriOrAlias` is defined as a Registry in the user settings.
      :Access Public Instance
      flag‚Üź‚ą®/EqualsAliasOrName uriOrAlias
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá {r}‚ÜźRemoveRegistry idOrUriOrAlias;bool
    ‚ćĚ Removes a Registry from the user settings.\\
    ‚ćĚ `‚ćĶ` can be either an id or a uri or an alias.\\
    ‚ćĚ `‚Üź` is 1 in case something was removed and 0 otherwise.
      :Access Public Instance
      :If 0=‚ČĘ_registries
          r‚Üź0
      :Else
          'You MUST NOT delete the very last registry!'Assert 1<‚ČĘ_registries
          :If 0=‚ČĘ_registries
              r‚Üź0
          :Else
              :If (‚äāidOrUriOrAlias)‚ąä_registries.id  ‚ćĚ Is it a UUID?
                  bool‚Üź_registries.id‚ČĘ¬®‚äāidOrUriOrAlias
              :Else
                  bool‚Üź~EqualsAliasOrName idOrUriOrAlias
              :EndIf
              _registries‚Üźbool/_registries
              r‚Üź‚ą®/~bool
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá r‚Üź{unique}GetRegistry idOrUriOrAlias;bool
    ‚ćĚ Returns a Registry (as a namespace) or `‚ć¨` in case the requested registry does not exist.
    ‚ćĚ `‚ćĶ` can be either a name or an alias.\\
    ‚ćĚ By default `idOrUriOrAlias` must be unique, but this can be overwritten with ‚ćļ‚Üź0
      :Access Public Instance
      unique‚Üź{0<‚éēNC ‚ćĶ:‚ćé‚ćĶ ‚čĄ 1}'unique'
      'No Registry defined in the user settings'Assert 0<‚ČĘ_registries
      :If ~‚ą®/bool‚Üź_registries.id‚Č°¬®‚äāidOrUriOrAlias   ‚ćĚ Is it a UUID?
      :AndIf 0=+/bool‚ÜźEqualsAliasOrName idOrUriOrAlias
          ('Registry <',idOrUriOrAlias,'> not found in user settings')Assert‚ą®/bool
      :EndIf
      'Unknown'Assert 0<+/bool
      'Found more than two Registries'Assert(~unique)‚ą®1=+/bool ‚ćĚ idOrUriOrAlias might be found more than once but with different aliases and API keys
      r‚Üź(bool‚ć≥1)‚äÉ_registries
    ‚ąá


    ‚ąá r‚ÜźDelete flag;filename;buff
    ‚ćĚ Call this in order to delete the currently instantiated user settings file.\\
    ‚ćĚ Returns 1 in case the file was successfully deleted otherwise (Blocked by another process, already deleted...)
      :Access Public Instance
      r‚Üź0
      :If flag
          filename‚Üź_path2config,cfg_name
      :AndIf F.IsFile filename
          r‚ÜźF.DeleteFile filename
          (‚äā'')F.NPUT(home.GetUserHomeFolder'.tatin')1
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá {r}‚ÜźSave flag;tmp;del;json
      :Access Public Instance
      r‚Üź‚ć¨
      :If flag
          json‚ÜźGetJSON5
          tmp‚Üź'tmp'F.GetTempFilename2 cfg_name
          {}(‚äājson)F.NPUT tmp 1
          {}F.DeleteFile path2config
          {}path2config(‚éēNMOVE home.Reg.F.ExecNfunction)tmp
          _fileTimestamp‚ÜźGetFileTimestamp _path2config
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá {r}‚ÜźMakeDefaultFile flag;defaultFolder
      :Access Public Instance
      ‚ćĚ Checks whether the current file is in a non-standard location. If that it the case it will create or overwrite
      ‚ćĚ any file `.tatin` in the default folder, and add the path to the current user settings file.
      r‚Üź0
      :If flag
          defaultFolder‚ÜźAddSlash home.GetUserHomeFolder''
      :AndIf ‚ČĘ/F.NormalizePath _path2config defaultFolder  ‚ćĚ Not in default folder?!
          (‚äā_path2config)F.NPUT(defaultFolder,'.tatin')1
          r‚Üź1
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

‚ćĚ ------------------- Private stuff

    Assert‚Üź{‚ćļ‚Üź‚äĘ ‚čĄ 0‚ąä‚ćĶ:‚ćļ ‚éēSIGNAL ErrorNo ‚čĄ shy‚Üź0}

    ‚ąá r‚ÜźGetJSON5;ns
      ns‚Üź‚éēNS''
      ns.registries‚Üź_registries
      ns.source‚Üź_source
      ns.caching‚Üź_caching
      ns.path2cache‚Üź_path2cache
      ns.license‚Üź_license
      r‚Üźhome.Reg.JSON ns
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá bool‚ÜźEqualsAliasOrName y;alias;uri;msg;uri_;port
    ‚ćĚ Returns a vector of booleans.\\
    ‚ćĚ Interprets `‚ćĶ` as an alias in case is carries `[]` and as an URI otherwise.
      :If '['‚ąäy
          alias‚Üź{‚éēC ‚ćĶ~'['}{‚ćĶ‚ÜĎ‚ć®¬Į1+‚ćĶ‚ć≥']'}y
          bool‚Üźalias‚ąė‚Č°¬®_registries.alias
      :Else
          uri‚ÜźF.EnforceSlash y
          :If ##.Reg.IsHTTP uri
              uri‚Üź{‚ćĶ/‚ć®3>+\‚ćĶ='/'}uri
          :EndIf
          uri‚ÜźAddSlash uri
          :If ':'‚ąähome.RemoveHttpProtocol uri
              port‚Üź‚äÉ(//)‚éēVFI{1‚Üď‚ćĶ‚ÜĎ‚ć®-':'‚ć≥‚ć®‚ĆĹ‚ćĶ}¬Į1‚Üďuri
          :Else
              port‚Üź0 80 443
          :EndIf
          uri_‚Üź':[0-9]+\/'‚éēR'/'‚ä£uri      ‚ćĚ Remove potential port number
          bool‚Üź(‚äāuri_)‚Č°¬®_registries.uri
          :If 1<‚ČĘport
              bool‚ąß‚Üź_registries.port‚ąä¬®‚äāport
          :Else
              bool‚ąß‚Üź_registries.port=port
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá {r}‚ÜźRead dummy;ns;b
    ‚ćĚ Reads the Client's config file
      r‚Üź‚ć¨
      ns‚Üź‚éēNS home.Reg.GetJsonFromFile path2config
      :If 0=ns.‚éēNC'license'
          ‚ćĚ Introduced in 2023-02
          ns.license‚Üź''
      :EndIf
      :If 0=ns.‚éēNC'maintainer'
          ‚ćĚ Introduced in 2023-10
          ns.maintainer‚Üź''
      :EndIf
      :If 0=ns.‚éēNC'group'
          ‚ćĚ Introduced in 2023-10
          ns.group‚Üź''
      :EndIf
      ns.registries.uri‚Üź{f‚Üź'\\'‚Č°2‚ćī‚ćĶ ‚čĄ AddSlash(f/'\\'),##.F.EnforceSlash(2√óf)‚Üď‚ćĶ}¬®ns.registries.uri
      :If 0<‚ČĘns.registries
          :If {(‚ČĘ‚ą™‚ćĶ)‚Č†‚ČĘ‚ćĶ}ns.registries.(uri alias)
              ('There are non-unique entries in ',path2config,' for uri+alias')Assert 0
          :EndIf
          _registries‚Üźns.registries[‚ćčns.registries.priority]
      :Else
          _registries‚Üź‚ć¨
      :EndIf
      _fileTimestamp‚ÜźGetFileTimestamp _path2config
      :If 0<‚ČĘ_registries
          :If 0<+/b‚Üź0=‚äÉ¬®_registries.‚éēNC‚äā'id'
              A(b/_registries).{‚éēTHIS.id‚Üź‚ćļ.Create_UUID}0  ‚ćĚ Was introduced in 0.74.0
          :EndIf
          _registries.alias‚Üź_registries.alias~¬®' '
          :If 0<+/b‚Üź0=‚äÉ¬®_registries.‚éēNC‚äā'noCaching'
              (b/_registries).{‚éēTHIS.noCaching‚Üź‚ćĶ}0  ‚ćĚ Was introduced in 0.63.0
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
      _source‚Üźns.source
      _license‚Üźns.license
      _group‚Üźns.group
      _maintainer‚Üźns.maintainer
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá r‚ÜźGetFileTimestamp filename
      r‚Üź3 ‚éēNINFO filename
    ‚ąá

    AddSlash‚Üź{‚ćĶ,(~(¬Į1‚ÜĎ‚ćĶ)‚ąä'/\')/'/'}

    ‚ąá {r}‚ÜźAddPrincipalServer dummy;buff;reg
